('turner-prize-2026', $g$Turner Prize 2026$g$, 'tate-britain', '2026-04-02', '2026-07-12', 18, 18, $g$https://www.tate.org.uk/whats-on/tate-britain$g$, 'mixed', ARRAY['contemporary','award','group-show']::text[], $g$Britain's most prestigious contemporary art award returns to Tate Britain with four shortlisted artists.$g$, $g$# Turner Prize 2026

Now in its 42nd year, the Turner Prize remains the UK's most important contemporary art award, celebrating the originality and vitality of art in Britain today.

This year's shortlist spans painting, sculpture, installation and moving image — an exhibition that asks urgent questions about identity, ecology and the futures we build together.$g$, ARRAY['Emii Alrai','Ingrid Pollard','Paul Maheke','Alvaro Barrington']::text[], $g$Linsey Young$g$, $g$https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1577720580479-7d839d829c73?w=1600&q=80$g$, $g$Contemporary sculpture in a gallery space$g$, null, true),
('hockney-late-works', $g$David Hockney: Late Works$g$, 'tate-modern', '2026-03-14', '2026-09-28', 22, 24, $g$https://www.tate.org.uk/whats-on/tate-modern$g$, 'painting', ARRAY['retrospective','british']::text[], $g$An intimate survey of Hockney's luminous work from the last decade, including new iPad compositions.$g$, $g$# David Hockney: Late Works

Spanning the past decade of Hockney's prolific practice, this exhibition brings together more than 80 paintings, drawings and digital works. The galleries chart a late flowering of colour and attention — a sustained looking at the ordinary miracles of light, landscape and company.$g$, ARRAY['David Hockney']::text[], null, $g$https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1501472312651-726afe119ff1?w=1600&q=80$g$, $g$Vibrant abstract painting with swirling colours$g$, null, false),
('women-in-revolt', $g$Women in Revolt!$g$, 'tate-modern', '2026-02-01', '2026-05-26', 16, null, $g$https://www.tate.org.uk/whats-on/tate-modern$g$, 'mixed', ARRAY['feminism','group-show','archival']::text[], $g$Art, activism and the women's movement in the UK, 1970–1990.$g$, $g$# Women in Revolt!

Drawing together more than 100 women artists, this landmark exhibition reveals the astonishing breadth of feminist artmaking in the UK between 1970 and 1990 — from photography and film to painting, performance and punk ephemera.$g$, null, null, $g$https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1578926375605-eaf7559b1458?w=1600&q=80$g$, $g$Archive posters and photographs on a gallery wall$g$, null, false),
('van-gogh-poets-lovers', $g$Van Gogh: Poets and Lovers$g$, 'national-gallery', '2026-01-20', '2026-05-03', 24, 28, $g$https://www.nationalgallery.org.uk/exhibitions$g$, 'painting', ARRAY['post-impressionist','historical']::text[], $g$A landmark gathering of Van Gogh's masterpieces exploring his visions of Arles and Saint-Rémy.$g$, $g$# Van Gogh: Poets and Lovers

Bringing together key works from Van Gogh's most fertile years, this exhibition follows his ambition to paint a modern art of feeling — the sunflowers, the starry nights, the letters to Theo. With more than 50 paintings and drawings, many rarely loaned.$g$, ARRAY['Vincent van Gogh']::text[], null, $g$https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1541680670548-88e8cd23c0f4?w=1600&q=80$g$, $g$Impressionist-style painting of sunflowers$g$, null, false),
('siena-medieval', $g$Siena: The Rise of Painting, 1300–1350$g$, 'national-gallery', '2026-03-08', '2026-06-22', 22, null, $g$https://www.nationalgallery.org.uk/exhibitions$g$, 'painting', ARRAY['medieval','historical']::text[], $g$Five decades that transformed European art, told through gilded altarpieces and tender saints.$g$, $g$# Siena: The Rise of Painting

In the early 14th century, a small group of artists working in Siena — Duccio, Simone Martini, the Lorenzetti brothers — reinvented what a painting could be. This exhibition gathers masterpieces from across Europe for the first time in a generation.$g$, null, null, $g$https://picsum.photos/seed/siena-medieval/1600/900$g$, $g$Medieval gold-leaf painting of figures$g$, null, false),
('fashioning-masculinities', $g$Fashioning Masculinities$g$, 'va', '2026-04-12', '2026-10-18', 20, null, $g$https://www.vam.ac.uk/exhibitions$g$, 'mixed', ARRAY['fashion','design']::text[], $g$Four centuries of menswear on display, from ruffs to runways.$g$, $g$# Fashioning Masculinities

Examining how clothes shape the way men — and those identifying as masculine — present themselves to the world, this exhibition draws on the V&A's encyclopaedic fashion collection, paired with paintings, photographs and film.$g$, null, null, $g$https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1558769132-cb1aea458c5e?w=1600&q=80$g$, $g$Tailored garments displayed on mannequins$g$, null, false),
('chanel-manifesto', $g$Gabrielle Chanel: Fashion Manifesto$g$, 'va', '2026-05-10', '2026-11-02', 26, 30, $g$https://www.vam.ac.uk/exhibitions$g$, 'mixed', ARRAY['fashion','retrospective']::text[], $g$The first UK exhibition devoted to the revolutionary work of Gabrielle 'Coco' Chanel.$g$, $g$# Gabrielle Chanel: Fashion Manifesto

Through nearly 200 looks spanning six decades, this show traces the evolution of Chanel's design vocabulary — the little black dress, the tweed suit, the No. 5 — and her radical idea that simplicity could be luxury.$g$, null, null, $g$https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1490481651871-ab68de25d43d?w=1600&q=80$g$, $g$A black and white gown displayed on a mannequin$g$, null, false),
('ra-summer-exhibition-2026', $g$Summer Exhibition 2026$g$, 'royal-academy', '2026-06-18', '2026-08-17', 22, null, $g$https://www.royalacademy.org.uk/exhibition/summer-exhibition-2026$g$, 'mixed', ARRAY['annual','group-show']::text[], $g$The world's oldest open-submission exhibition, held without interruption since 1769.$g$, $g$# Summer Exhibition 2026

Over 1,000 works from both emerging and established artists, selected from thousands of open submissions. A chaotic, exhilarating snapshot of art being made in the UK right now.$g$, null, null, $g$https://picsum.photos/seed/ra-summer-2026/1600/900$g$, $g$Paintings densely hung salon-style on gallery walls$g$, null, false),
('ai-weiwei-making-sense', $g$Ai Weiwei: Making Sense$g$, 'royal-academy', '2026-02-28', '2026-05-18', 22, 25, $g$https://www.royalacademy.org.uk/exhibition/ai-weiwei$g$, 'installation', ARRAY['contemporary','political']::text[], $g$A major new survey examining the artist's obsession with objects, value and cultural meaning.$g$, $g$# Ai Weiwei: Making Sense

Five vast 'fields' of objects — porcelain cannonballs, Stone Age tools, smashed Han dynasty jars — invite viewers to reflect on craft, destruction, heritage, and what we choose to preserve.$g$, ARRAY['Ai Weiwei']::text[], null, $g$https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1531058020387-3be344556be6?w=1600&q=80$g$, $g$Large-scale installation of ceramic objects arranged on a gallery floor$g$, null, false),
('serpentine-pavilion-2026', $g$Serpentine Pavilion 2026$g$, 'serpentine', '2026-06-06', '2026-10-26', null, null, null, 'installation', ARRAY['architecture','free-entry','annual']::text[], $g$The 25th edition of the annual architectural commission in Kensington Gardens.$g$, $g$# Serpentine Pavilion 2026

A 25-year tradition, the Pavilion is unveiled each summer as a living space for performance, dialogue and rest. This year's design by a leading international architect will be revealed in June.$g$, null, null, $g$https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1518780664697-55e3ad937233?w=1600&q=80$g$, $g$Contemporary architectural pavilion in a London park$g$, null, false),
('kapoor-forms', $g$Anish Kapoor: Forms$g$, 'serpentine', '2026-04-03', '2026-09-07', null, null, null, 'sculpture', ARRAY['contemporary','free-entry']::text[], $g$New sculpture by one of the most influential artists working today.$g$, $g$# Anish Kapoor: Forms

This exhibition brings together recent sculpture exploring voids, pigment and pure geometry. Kapoor's objects are both objects and absences — they pull the gaze inward.$g$, ARRAY['Anish Kapoor']::text[], null, $g$https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1582582621959-48d27397dc69?w=1600&q=80$g$, $g$Minimalist sculpture with polished reflective surface$g$, null, false),
('hayward-mixing-it-up', $g$Mixing It Up: Painting Today$g$, 'hayward', '2026-03-20', '2026-06-28', 17, 19, $g$https://www.southbankcentre.co.uk/whats-on$g$, 'painting', ARRAY['contemporary','group-show']::text[], $g$Thirty-one painters working in Britain today, charting the medium's unruly vitality.$g$, $g$# Mixing It Up: Painting Today

From figuration to abstraction, from intimate portraits to expansive landscapes, this exhibition asks what painting means now — in a moment saturated with images, where the painted mark still insists on time, touch, attention.$g$, null, null, $g$https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1536924940846-227afb31e2a5?w=1600&q=80$g$, $g$Contemporary painting with bold colours on gallery wall$g$, null, false),
('whitechapel-nicole-eisenman', $g$Nicole Eisenman: What Happened$g$, 'whitechapel', '2026-04-18', '2026-08-10', null, null, null, 'painting', ARRAY['contemporary','free-entry']::text[], $g$The first UK survey of the American painter's restless, wickedly perceptive work.$g$, $g$# Nicole Eisenman: What Happened

Eisenman's paintings and sculptures track a generation — its parties, protests, intimacies and anxieties — with tenderness, humour and an unerring eye for the absurd.$g$, ARRAY['Nicole Eisenman']::text[], null, $g$https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1549490349-8643362247b5?w=1600&q=80$g$, $g$Large expressive figurative painting$g$, null, false),
('saatchi-flowers', $g$Flowers — Flora in Contemporary Art$g$, 'saatchi', '2026-05-15', '2026-09-20', 15, 18, $g$https://saatchigallery.com/exhibitions$g$, 'mixed', ARRAY['contemporary','group-show','nature']::text[], $g$Thirty contemporary artists reimagine the botanical across painting, sculpture and moving image.$g$, $g$# Flowers

A lush gathering of recent work that uses flora — as motif, metaphor and material — to think through ecology, memory, and the porous line between natural and cultural worlds.$g$, null, null, $g$https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1490750967868-88aa4486c946?w=1600&q=80$g$, $g$Close-up of a contemporary painting featuring botanical imagery$g$, null, false),
('courtauld-cezanne', $g$Cézanne: Drawing$g$, 'courtauld', '2026-02-14', '2026-05-05', 14, 16, $g$https://courtauld.ac.uk/whats-on$g$, 'painting', ARRAY['impressionist','drawing']::text[], $g$Cézanne's drawings and watercolours — the private engine behind the paintings.$g$, $g$# Cézanne: Drawing

Over 80 drawings and watercolours reveal how Cézanne thought on paper — sketching apples, Mont Sainte-Victoire, his own hand — working out the problems that would preoccupy modern art for a century.$g$, ARRAY['Paul Cézanne']::text[], null, $g$https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1577720580479-7d839d829c73?w=1600&q=80$g$, $g$Framed drawings hanging in a gallery$g$, null, false),
('photographers-gallery-deutsche-2026', $g$British Photography Now$g$, 'whitechapel', '2026-05-10', '2026-07-27', null, null, null, 'photography', ARRAY['contemporary','group-show','free-entry']::text[], $g$New work from twelve photographers mapping the textures of contemporary British life.$g$, $g$# British Photography Now

